                id: 115,
                title: "The Underwater Discovery (K)",
                text: "Maya had always been fascinated by the ocean. When her marine biologist aunt invited her on a research expedition, she could barely contain her excitement. They were studying coral reefs off the coast of Florida. On the boat, Aunt Rosa explained that coral reefs were dying around the world due to warming oceans and pollution. Scientists were trying to find ways to help them recover. Maya learned to use snorkeling gear and dove into the crystal-clear water. The underwater world took her breath away. Colorful fish darted between coral formations that looked like alien landscapes. She saw sea turtles gliding gracefully and tiny seahorses hiding in the seaweed. On the third day, Maya noticed something unusual. A section of coral that looked dead and white had small patches of new growth. She called Aunt Rosa over to look. Her aunt got very excited. This was exactly what the research team had been searching for. They took samples and photographs. Back in the lab, they discovered that certain bacteria were helping the coral heal itself. This discovery could help scientists develop new ways to restore dying reefs around the world. Maya's observation became part of a scientific paper. She learned that important discoveries can come from anyone who pays attention and asks questions. That summer changed her life. She decided she wanted to become a marine biologist too.",
