                id: 116,
                title: "The Escape Room Champions (K)",
                text: "The Garcia siblings had one hour to escape from the locked room. Fourteen-year-old Elena, twelve-year-old Carlos, and ten-year-old Sofia had been given this escape room challenge as a birthday present. The theme was an ancient Egyptian tomb, and they needed to solve puzzles to find their way out. At first, they argued about what to do. Carlos wanted to search everywhere immediately. Sofia thought they should read all the clues first. Elena tried to do everything herself. Ten minutes passed with no progress. Then Elena had an idea. What if they each focused on what they did best? Carlos was great at finding hidden objects. Sofia loved reading and word puzzles. Elena was good at math and logic problems. They started working as a team. Carlos discovered a hidden compartment behind a painting. Inside was a scroll with hieroglyphics that Sofia decoded to reveal numbers. Elena used those numbers to unlock a combination lock on a treasure chest. Working together, they solved puzzle after puzzle. A maze led them to a key. A riddle revealed which key fit which lock. A pattern recognition challenge opened a secret door. With three minutes left, they faced the final puzzle. It required all three of them to press buttons simultaneously in different corners of the room. They counted down together and pressed at exactly the same moment. The exit door swung open. They had escaped with time to spare. The staff said they were the youngest team to ever complete that room.",
