                id: 234,
                title: "Coming Out (V)",
                text: "The words had lived inside Jaylen for so long that actually speaking them felt like releasing a held breath. 'Mom, Dad... I'm gay.' The silence that followed stretched interminably, though probably only seconds passed. His mother's expression cycled through emotions too quickly to read. His father stared at his hands. This moment, which Jaylen had rehearsed in his mind for years, felt nothing like the imagined versions‚Äîneither the cathartic relief nor the feared rejection, just overwhelming vulnerability. His mother spoke first. 'How long have you known?' 'Since I was about fourteen. I've been sure since sixteen.' She nodded slowly, processing. 'Why didn't you tell us sooner?' The question held no accusation, only hurt‚Äîshe'd thought they had the kind of relationship where secrets weren't necessary. Jaylen tried to explain the fear: fear of disappointment, of changed relationships, of becoming a different person in their eyes. Fear that love, once considered unconditional, might have conditions after all. His father finally looked up. 'You're still my son. Nothing changes that.' The statement, simple as it was, released something in Jaylen's chest. 'But I need time to... adjust my expectations, I suppose. I had a picture of your future‚Äîmarriage, grandchildren‚Äîand I need to let go of that specific picture.' 'There can still be marriage and grandchildren,' Jaylen said softly. 'They might just look different than you imagined.' The conversation continued for hours, awkward and painful and ultimately healing. Coming out wasn't a single moment but a process‚Äîand this was just the beginning.",
